Nikki and I talked today, and post conversation I realized that on Tuesday, the OG's and I are going out to a group lunch, and it will be the last time we're ever together on the first day of school. The last time. It sounds so final, whether I'm saying it in my head or out loud. I mean, I have so many friends that I love to pieces, but somehow, it always comes back to the OG's. They're like, these amazing people who are just always there. They don't even have to physically be near me to have this huge affect on my life. I mean, when I do something stupid, I can imagine Aggie rolling her eyes at me and smirking. And when I do or say something funny, I can see Nikki crackin up right along with me. Everytime I drive by St. Rene's I think of Laura and Mare, and us making fun of Krystyna for being in angel choir. And God, practically every time I think of dancing or school or something completely random like drawing black circles on cd's so you can burn them, I think of Julie, ever so charming, even when she's being completely retarded. I guess I just realized how different things will be once we graduate. I'm going to miss them so much, they all mean the absolute world to me. There are times when I love them more than my own family, and that is something that will always connect me to them. Wherever life ends up taking us, even if we aren't friends, we'll still be friends, as weird as that sounds. They are part of me. Past, present, and future. And today I realized just how impossibly amazing they are and they just keep getting better. So yeah, I love all my friends: Mina, Kasia, Sue, Pri, Sarah, Kim, Lindsey everybody a whole lot. But the OG's will always have this place in my life, and my heart, that will never change. So to end this completely....nostalgic and probably boring entry, I just want to say one thing. You guys mean the world to me, and I love you so much. Ok I'm done rambling now. :)

That was my epiphany of the day. So anyway, Aya is leaving tomorrow. Which sucks. I'm really going to miss her and all her weird, annoying, funny, retarded antics. So right now I am in the middle of a huge bout of wanderlust and I can't seem to snap out of it. That's why I am going to inquire about staying out west for the majority of the summer. When I close my eyes these days all I can see is sipping Pina Coladas in my step aunt's sprawling stucco ranch, swimming in the Nevada-shaped pool, spending the entire summer lounging about, and finally getting away from the stress that my year has been comprised of. This year I realized that I'm not going to be able to get into a good college, so Macomb is really my only option. I didn't get into AP English, which further killed my dreams. I can only hope that I'm a "late bloomer" and that my time to be successful will come soon. I need a break. School has never been so...exhausting. This whole year has been one big emotional and physical rollercoaster. Sometimes when I wake up in the morning I would rather die than drag myself out of bed. I think that all the stress and anxiety is going to boil over one day and I'm just going to crack. Chances are, it won't be pretty when I do. In conclusion, I want to go away this summer. I need a mental health...summer. I have to save what little sanity I have left.
